    "Lloyd R. Bailey": "), and utter terror among the survivors (vv. 36-\n37). Such extreme and excessive actions may\nrepulse the modern reader and seem unworthy\nof a biblical Deity who is otherwise described by\nsuch attributes as love, justice, and forgiveness.\nIt is therefore necessary, for proper under-\nstanding, to place these threats in their context:\n(1) Four previous threats are expressed, each\nbecoming more severe after such remarks as,\n\u201cAnd if in spite of this you will not obey me, I\nwill continue to punish you\u201d (vv. 18, 21, 23,"
